reviews:
[{'Reviewer': 'Pritam Shetty', 'Rating': '5.0 ', 'Date': 'Reviewed in India on 30 September 2023', 'Review': "I recently made the switch from Android to the iPhone 14 Plus, and it has been a remarkably smooth transition. Here are some key points about my experience:

1. Seamless Setup: Setting up my new iPhone was a breeze. Apple's migration tool effortlessly transferred all my contacts, photos, and apps from my Android device. It was a stress-free process that ensured I didn't lose any important data.

2. Intuitive User Interface: The iOS interface on the iPhone 14 Plus is incredibly user-friendly. Navigating through the device, customizing settings, and finding apps is straightforward, even for someone who was accustomed to Android.

3. Performance: The iPhone 14 Plus packs a powerful punch. The device runs smoothly, and apps load quickly. Multitasking is a breeze, thanks to the robust hardware and optimized software.

4. Display: The OLED display on the iPhone 14 Plus is stunning. Colors are vibrant, and the screen is sharp and clear. It's a joy to use for watching videos, browsing, and gaming.

5. Camera: The camera quality on the iPhone 14 Plus is exceptional. The photos and videos captured are rich in detail and clarity. The advanced camera features and modes provide ample opportunities for creativity.

6. App Ecosystem: The App Store offers a vast selection of high-quality apps that enhance the iPhone experience. I found all my favorite Android apps and discovered some excellent iOS exclusives.

7. Privacy and Security: Apple's commitment to user privacy and security is evident. Features like App Tracking Transparency and Face ID add an extra layer of protection.

8. Battery Life: The battery life on the iPhone 14 Plus is impressive. I can comfortably go through a day of heavy usage without worrying about running out of power.

In conclusion, my transition from Android to the iPhone 14 Plus has been a positive one. The device offers a premium experience with a top-notch camera, excellent performance, and an ecosystem that keeps everything well-integrated. If you're considering the switch, I highly recommend it for a seamless and satisfying smartphone experience.

About this item
The next-gen imaging in the realme 12 Pro Series was made for cinematic portrait shots. We specifically tuned the imaging in the realme 12 Pro Series for true-to-life results, with great color and clarity, and for a dramatic cinematic effect with great texture.

The 3D Jubilee Bracelet gives the realme 12 Pro Series a truly unique taste. More sophisticated than the previous generation, diamond patterns running seamlessly across the back of the phone, capturing the texture of luxury watch straps.

I live in outskirts and I don't get 5g inside the house (in the extreme end of the rooms with realme 9i 5g, mind that I get full 5g in the drawing room and other rooms except the room which is very much inside) so my primary purpose was 5g inside the house, which I am getting now with oppo a3 pro. I don't do heavy gaming rather some light games and they are running fine. Below I am pointing the pros and cons for others to find helpful:
Pros :
1) 5g network : Firstly in outskirts of west bengal you will never get jio, or voda so try airtel and airtel only. I am getting 24 hours 5g even in burrow holes. So, you will get airtel 5g in this phone.
2) Battery : Decent battery and even if you play mild games it must serve you one day.
3) Design : It may not matter to many but the design is very eye-catching.
4) Camera : Decent. I will give 3/5. I am not a fan of camera.
5) Sound - Very loud sound.
6) Very sturdy and splash proof ip 54 rating.

Cons :
1) Price - Most important thing is it very very overpriced. Market price is â‚¹21000. Which is very costly if you ask me. I got it at â‚¹17k but still it is not worth it, for many people as the features are not much to speak of.
2) Processor is not up to the mark as per pricing. Heavy gaming will lag and may be even heat up (I didn't test it)
3) Charger is not 45W - Even though the charger says 45W charging but, when I checked the adapter it says 5V=2A or 9V=4.1A which means if you have low voltage it will charge slow and even if it is okay it is not 45w, but something around 40W. Charged 20% to 100% in 1hour 50 minutes. There is no logo on the adapter or cord
4) Hybrid Sim Slot - I checked in online site and did not know (my mistake though but still) so you can either have two Sims or one sim and a sd card (1tb expandable).

Verdict - If you can afford 2k more and don't have any reservations about better network then go for iqoo z9. It has lesser 5g bands so I bought this or else iqoo z9 is much better than this, go for it.

It has so many Quality-of-Life changes built into the phone that I would've never thought about. Here's some examples:
- It has adaptive charging, which means it calculates the perfect rate to charge the phone so that it can charge to 100% before your next alarm will trigger
- Even though adaptive charging is on by default, it has the option to disable it temporarily so that you can do a quick fast charge if you're in a rush
- It tells you up until what time the phone will last until with the charge left on it
- When you copy something, it has a shortcut button to paste it immediately instead of having to hold down on the screen
- Taking a screenshot and cropping is so much faster
